identifications.body: iNaturalist uses very similar common names for two Smilax species, which I think is too bad.  Smilax glauca, which iNaturalist calls "Sawbrier" but I know as "blue Smilax" has a very easily identified chalky blue underside to the leaf, and never has prickly leaves.  Smilax bona-nox, which iNaturalist calls "Saw greenbrier" and I know as "Catbrier" doesn't have a pale underside but frequently has prickly leaves.  Both species have prickles on the stem.  This plant is S. bona-nox.
